President Joe Biden and President Pedro Sánchez of Spain held a conversation regarding the ongoing situation in Afghanistan. They commended the efforts of their personnel in Kabul who are collaborating to evacuate their citizens, Afghans who supported the EU mission, and other vulnerable Afghan individuals. President Biden specifically acknowledged Spain's leadership in garnering international support for Afghan women and girls. He also expressed gratitude to President Sánchez for Spain's assistance in providing temporary housing for at-risk Afghans bound for the United States at military bases in Rota and Moron.